      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S represents a pinnacle of analog feedback and mechanical refinement. Powered by a mid-mounted 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, the engine exhibits zero bore scoring and has been proactively fitted with a dual-row IMS bearing retrofit. Power is delivered through a crisp 6-speed manual transaxle to an all-wheel-drive system that maintains perfect torque vectoring. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, featuring factory-spec Bilstein dampers and refreshed bushings that ensure surgical turn-in. Braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of thermal stress. This is a true turn-key example with a flawless DME report, offering a visceral driving experience for the discerning purist.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
