      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera represents the pinnacle of the analog driving experience. Featuring the 3.6L M96/03 naturally aspirated flat-six, this unit has been fastidiously maintained with a proactive LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal (RMS). The G96 six-speed manual transaxle offers crisp, mechanical engagement, sending power to the rear wheels through an optional factory limited-slip differential. The chassis remains impeccably tight, retaining its original Bilstein-sourced dampers and factory-spec bushings. The paint depth is consistent across all panels, and the undercarriage is devoid of any oxidation or fluid weepage. With a comprehensive service dossier and recent bore-scoping results showing zero scoring, this is a collector-grade example for the discerning purist.",
